<title>USA: Shoe Carnival margins below expectations.</title>
<headline>Shoe Carnival margins below expectations.</headline>
<dateline>EVANSVILLE, Ind. 1997-01-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shoe Carnival Inc said its gross profit margins were below original expectations for the month of December because of a strong promotional retail climate.</p>
<p>But it said gross profit margins were significantly improved over the prior year.</p>
<p>President Mark Lemond said inventories were 16 percent lower than last year going into the clearance month of January.</p>
<p>Earlier Thursday, the retailer said same-store sales for the five weeks ended January 6, 1996 rose 3.8 percent.</p>
<p>	     ((Chicago newsdesk 312 408-8787))</p>
